Vestas CEO Defends U.S. Investments, Says Led to Orders: Borsen

-- B y   G e l u   S u l u g i u c
-- 
2011-03-30T05:54:21Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-30/vestas-ceo-defends-u-s-investments-says-led-to-orders-borsen.html
Vestas Wind Systems A/S Chief
Executive Officer Ditlev Engel defended investments of 15
billion kroner ($2.8 billion) over three years, saying many of
the company’s turbine orders this year wouldn’t have come if it
didn’t have its new factories in the  United States , Borsen
reported today citing an interview with Engel.  Engel added that Vestas has no plans to raise new capital,
Copenhagen-based Borsen reported.     Click here for web link  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
